metadata.name: 420 Solar Eclipse II 1/69
metadata.description: This NFT is of the hybrid solar eclipse that occurred over Australia on 4/20/2023 as seen from the Perth Observatory in Bickley, Western Australia.  Another 4/20 hybrid solar eclipse will not happen until the year 2111.  This image captures the "Bailey's Beads" effect created by the moon's mountain ranges being outlined against the sun's orb.  Owning this image and 420 Solar Eclipse I in the same wallet may entitle you to an allowlist, discount, or perhaps free drop of future smallforest project physical issues (will require a valid US mailing address).  There are 2 NFTs issued to commemorate this event.  They are the world's first and second ever solar eclipse NFTs.
